# Sprint 3: About, Projects Listing, Skills, Contact Pages

## Human-Supplied Values

The following values must be provided by the human before the agent executes the scopes that require them. The agent uses these exact token names as placeholders wherever a real value is needed. The human replaces the tokens before the site goes live (Sprint 4).

| Token | Used in | Required before |
|---|---|---|
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_BIO` | About page bio paragraph | Scope 1 |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_SKILLS` | SkillsGrid technologies array | Scope 1 |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_RESUME` | `public/resume.pdf` | Sprint 4 deploy |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_LINKEDIN` | Contact page LinkedIn link | Scope 3 |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_GITHUB` | Contact page GitHub link | Scope 3 |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_EMAIL` | Contact page email + Formspree fallback | Scopes 3 & 5 |
| `HUMAN_SUPPLY_FORMSPREE` | Formspree fetch endpoint URL | Scope 5 |

The agent writes these tokens literally in the source code as string values or comments. Example:
```js
const technologies = ["HUMAN_SUPPLY_SKILLS"];
```
```html
<p>HUMAN_SUPPLY_BIO</p>
```
```js
const FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT = "HUMAN_SUPPLY_FORMSPREE";
const CONTACT_EMAIL = "HUMAN_SUPPLY_EMAIL";
```

## UX Flows

1. [About]: User clicks About → sees bio paragraph → sees grid of technology tags → clicks resume link → downloads PDF
2. [Projects]: User clicks Projects → sees Sanglogium hero card → clicks card → navigates to case study
3. [Skills]: User clicks Skills → sees a simple static page of skills/technologies content
4. [Contact]: User clicks Contact → sees email, LinkedIn, GitHub links → sees contact form → fills form → submits → sees success feedback (or error with `mailto:` fallback)
5. [Form validation]: User submits empty form → sees inline validation errors → fills required fields → submits successfully
6. [Mobile]: All pages readable on mobile; skills grid wraps; project card is full-width; form inputs are full-width and tappable

## End-State Overview

Four static pages: About (bio + SkillsGrid + resume link), Projects listing (Sanglogium hero card, no additional cards), Skills (simplest possible static content page), Contact (social links + Formspree-backed form with client-side validation).

## Architecture Contract

- **About**: Static content, `SkillsGrid.astro` component (CSS Grid tags, no JS)
- **Projects**: Static content, `ProjectCard.astro` component (zero JS, `<a>` wrapper); no additional cards beyond Sanglogium in this sprint
- **Skills**: Static `skills.astro` page — simplest possible; no component extraction needed; just Base layout + semantic HTML content; can be expanded later
- **Contact**: Static links + `ContactForm.astro` (vanilla JS, `fetch` to Formspree)
- **Resume**: `public/resume.pdf` placeholder from Sprint 0; replaced by human with real PDF before Sprint 4
- **Formspree**: `fetch` POST to `HUMAN_SUPPLY_FORMSPREE` endpoint; client-side validation before submit

### File contracts
- `src/pages/about.astro` — bio text + `<SkillsGrid>` + resume download link
- `src/components/SkillsGrid.astro` — CSS Grid of technology name tags from a `technologies` array prop
- `src/pages/projects.astro` — Sanglogium hero card only; `<!-- TODO: add more project cards here -->` comment below it
- `src/components/ProjectCard.astro` — accepts `href`, `title`, `description`, `imageSrc` props; `<a>` wrapper, zero JS
- `src/pages/skills.astro` — simplest possible static page: Base layout + heading + content; no sub-components needed
- `src/pages/contact.astro` — social links + `<ContactForm>`
- `src/components/ContactForm.astro` — form HTML + vanilla JS validation + Formspree fetch

## Scope Contracts

### Scope Contract 1: About Page + Skills Grid

**UX Slice**
- User sees bio paragraph
- User sees grid of technology tags
- User clicks resume link → placeholder PDF downloads

**Architecture Slice**
- `about.astro`: `<BaseLayout title="About" />` + `<p>HUMAN_SUPPLY_BIO</p>` + `<SkillsGrid>` + resume link
- Resume link: `<a href="/resume.pdf" download>Download Resume</a>`
- `SkillsGrid.astro`: `technologies` prop (array of strings); maps to `<span>` tags in a CSS Grid
- Tailwind Grid: `grid-cols-3 sm:grid-cols-4 md:grid-cols-5 gap-3`
- Tag styling: `rounded-lg border px-3 py-1 text-sm`
- Technologies array value: `["HUMAN_SUPPLY_SKILLS"]` — one element with the token; human replaces with real array before go-live

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] Bio paragraph visible (shows token `HUMAN_SUPPLY_SKILLS` placeholder — correct at this stage)
- [ ] Technology tags grid visible; tags wrap correctly on mobile
- [ ] Resume link triggers download of placeholder PDF
- [ ] No JS errors on page

