### Scope Contract 5: Contact Form — HTML + Validation

**UX Slice**
- User sees form with Name, Email, Message fields
- Submit empty form → inline validation errors appear
- Fill fields → errors clear

**Architecture Slice**
- `ContactForm.astro`: `<form>` with three fields + submit button + honeypot
- Fields: Name (`type="text" name="name"`), Email (`type="email" name="email"`), Message (`<textarea name="message">`)
- Honeypot: `<input name="website" style="display:none" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">` — hidden from users; if non-empty on submit, abort silently without calling fetch
- Vanilla JS: `form.addEventListener('submit', handler)`
- Validation: Name required, Email required + basic format check, Message required
- Error display: `<span class="error-msg">` next to each field, toggled via JS classList; initially hidden
- No external validation library

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] All 3 fields + submit button visible
- [ ] Submit empty → validation errors appear next to each empty field
- [ ] Fill Name only → Email and Message still show errors
- [ ] Fill all correctly → all errors clear
- [ ] Honeypot field hidden in DOM; not visible or tabbable to users

---

### Scope Contract 6: Contact Form — Formspree Submission

**UX Slice**
- Valid form → submit → success message replaces form
- Network error or blocked fetch → error message + visible `mailto:` fallback link; form values retained
- Button disabled during submission (no double-submit)

**Architecture Slice**
- Constants at top of script:
  ```js
  const FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT = "HUMAN_SUPPLY_FORMSPREE";
  const CONTACT_EMAIL = "HUMAN_SUPPLY_EMAIL";
  ```
- If honeypot is non-empty: abort silently, do not call fetch, do not show any message
- `fetch()` POST to `FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT` with JSON `{ name, email, message }`
- Submit button disabled during fetch; re-enabled on error
- Success: replace form HTML with `<p>Message sent — thank you!</p>`
- Error: show error message + `<a href="mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}">Send email directly</a>` fallback; restore form values
- ClientRouter state reset: on `astro:page-load`, reset form to initial state (clear fields, remove success/error messages, re-enable submit button)
- Inline script size: the total JS in this component must be under 2KB — verify by checking the source file character count (not DevTools network bundle)

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] Submit valid form → fetch request visible in Network tab (to `HUMAN_SUPPLY_FORMSPREE` placeholder URL — will 404, that is expected)
- [ ] Button disabled during fetch, re-enabled on error
- [ ] Success message replaces form after successful response
- [ ] Error message + `mailto:` fallback link visible when fetch fails (simulate: block request in DevTools → Network → right-click request → Block)
- [ ] Form values preserved on error (not cleared)
- [ ] Navigate away after success, then back → form resets to fresh empty state
- [ ] Honeypot filled → no network request made (verify: fill hidden field via DevTools console, submit, check Network tab)
- [ ] Source file character count for the `<script>` block is under 2,000 characters

## Continuous Verification

- After each scope contract: run `astro dev`, verify checklist
- After all scopes: navigate between About, Projects, Skills, Contact via nav + direct URL
- Verify total JS on each page via DevTools Network tab → should be approximately 13KB (ClientRouter only; contact form script is inline Astro island)

## Simplicity Guardrails

- Is SkillsGrid the simplest possible? (Yes: array map to `<span>` tags, zero JS)
- Is ProjectCard the simplest possible? (Yes: `<a>` wrapper, static content, zero JS)
- Is Skills page the simplest possible? (Yes: Base layout + static HTML, no components, no JS)
- Is contact form the simplest possible? (Yes: vanilla JS, no framework form library, under 2KB)
- Is Formspree integration the simplest possible? (Yes: single `fetch` POST, no wrapper library)
